string.name: STR_ZONE_COMMENT_TizeridB
string.body: Tijerid Central Area links the main gate and the city, and it is also where the Eljeris Military Academy which symbolizes the power of Tijerid is located. The military academy is the base of the Red Flame Brigade and the Blood Sky Templars, but it also functions as a public educational facility for Tijerid citizens and the masters of all Classes teach their skills here as well. The academy also has an expansive drill ground for training, and on either side of the academy there are arcades of Collecting and Craft related guilds.

string.name: STR_ZONE_COMMENT_FF1
string.body: A dry and barren wilderness constantly swept by gales, its name comes from the sound of the wind passing underneath the great gorge that sometimes echoes like the roaring of a maddened beast. There are mines in the fissures on the ground of the great gorge, and there is a road leading back to Tijerid for the transport of minerals extracted from the mines. The Tursin Krall that have lairs throughout the region are known to raid the adventurers or supply-transport wagons. Tijeridians have been fighting them for a long time, but eradicating the numerous Krall who have settled in the area for generations has proven impossible and as a result they continue to coexist if not harmoniously.

string.name: STR_ZONE_COMMENT_FF2
string.body: A vast wasteland where a fierce battle had taken place during the Elyos-Asmodian War, it is infested with numerous wild beasts and Krall but the Guard Posts scattered in various locations protect the Elyos from getting harmed. Lewindal Stonefort was built after the Krall invasion to further strengthen the defense of the city, and it is a safe place with many stationed guards as well as a center of active resource management. Moreover, it is where the lifeline of Tijerid, Cheravic Docks, is located, which receives the resources arriving from other countries by ships and sends them to the city by road. The wasteland is divided into two halves where the opposing Elyos and Krall have taken the north and south respectively.

string.name: STR_ZONE_COMMENT_FF3
string.body: This geothermal area used to be an ordinary wasteland a long time ago, but the Cataclysm had caused the lava of the Red Mountains to overflow and turned the whole region into a land of death where life finds it difficult to survive. Plants either burned or turned into ashes, the heated earth gushes out smoke and gas if not covered by hardened lava, and the magma inside the Mouth of the Fregion cave flowed out to block the path to the Holy Ground. The gorge in the northeast of the area is occupied by the Kaidan Krall, and there is a Village of Kobolds to the south of the gorge. The front of the path leading to the Mouth of Fregion is where the well-renowned attraction of the area, the Kobold Inn, is found.

string.name: STR_ZONE_COMMENT_EE2
string.body: It has been a long while since the people of Erole built the Outer Castle and begun to develop the surrounding areas to expand their living space. Maybe it is due to bad fengshui, but despite a favorable natural environment a continuous stream of inexplicable accidents disrupted the development process and the fruits of their labor are only evident inside the Outer Castle. The ruins of facilities used for development and half-finished buildings are commonly found, and the only thing still intact is the road laid for the transport of materials. Yet they still managed to complete the Lighthouse, which is used for keeping a watch on the surroundings and there are guards regularly patrolling the road between the Outer Castle and the Lighthouse.

string.name: STR_ZONE_COMMENT_TizeridBL
string.body: The left area of Tijerid comprises of residential blocks for commoners and a central market street busy with small street vendors selling food, weapons and various other items. There is also a dock to the north where goods imported from other countries are received, and the biggest tavern in all of Tijerid can be found on the road between the market street and the dock.

string.name: STR_ZONE_COMMENT_TizeridBR
string.body: The right area of Tijerid comprises of a market street occupied by many high-end stores including a Soul Healing clinic, and the northern part of the area boasts a gladiatorial arena that maybe regarded as the flower of Tijeridian cultural experience, and luxurious mansions of nobles and a martial arts gym are also located nearby. However, a corner district that has turned into a slum area displays a dark side of Tijerid as well.

string.name: STR_ZONE_Comment_IDAb1_Dreadgion
string.body: The Dredgion of the Baranath Legion, who are terrorizing Reshanta. Elyos and Asmodians must kill its captain, Adhati, while keeping each other in check. Abyss Points are up for grabs.
